doc.after: Marojejy National Park is noted for its rich biodiversity, which can appeal to both scientist and ecotourist.[2][25] There are a wide range of habitats within the park, and many of its plants and animals are endemic to the area.[17] Scientific expeditions regularly discover species that are either not previously documented in Marojejy, or in some cases, completely new to science. Some new species are highly endangered. In the case of many large groups, such as invertebrates, very little is known and much remains to be discovered.[26]
